  "title": "Booking Scheme",
  "description": "A booking schema (also called posting schema, accounting schema, or journal entry template) is a set of predefined accounting rules that tell a system which accounts to debit and credit when a specific business event occurs.\r\n\r\nA Booking Schema is a predefined set of rules or templates that determine how financial transactions from business events are posted to accounts in the ledger.\r\nIt maps business events (like loans, payments, fees, or sales) to the correct ledger accounts and often specifies:\r\n\r\n- Debit and credit accounts\r\n\r\n- Posting rules (amounts, dimensions, currencies)\r\n\r\n- Transaction types and subledger sources\r\n\r\nIn essence, a booking schema translates business events into accounting entries.",
